                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename> de <surname>Herwell</surname>
                        </persName>, with the assent of 
               <persName nymRef="Herwell">
                           <forename>Christiana</forename> his wife</persName>, grants to 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Amicia</forename>, the prioress</persName>, and the
                        <orgName key="org_107016">nuns of St. Mary and St. Nicholas of Littlemor</orgName>, in alms, with two
               of his daughters to be made nuns of the same house, one messuage and half a hide of
               land, and so much meadow as pertains to one hide of land in <placeName key="place_109508">Sydenham</placeName>, and another
               messuage which <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename>, lord of <placeName type="lord">Hancepe</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
               held of him in the same village, paying annually one penny at Easter, and to the chief lords of the
               fee one pound of pepper. For this donation the prioress gave ta him 60 marks of silver beforehand. 
               Witness.
               <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Saunford</surname>
                        </persName> etc.
               (<origDate notBefore="1230" notAfter="1240" precision="low">c. 1230-40</origDate>.) 
               .</p>
